The Samsung Galaxy Note 10 Lite is set to launch in South Africa in the first week of February at a recommended retail price of R12,999. Cellucity has revealed the specifications of the Galaxy Note 10 Lite that will be sold through Vodacom in South Africa. At launch, the Galaxy Note 10 Lite will be sold with 8GB RAM and 128GB internal storage. The retailer also revealed that the Galaxy Note 10 Lite will be available on contract from R599 per month. Similar to the Samsung Galaxy A71, the Note 10 Lite features a 4,500mAh battery. It is also similar in size to the Galaxy A71 and a bit thicker. That is where the similarities end, though. The Galaxy Note 10 Lite uses a triple-camera system, has a faster processor, more RAM, and supports the Samsung S Pen. The three cameras of the Samsung Galaxy Note 10 Lite are configured as follows (AF is autofocus, OIS is optical image stabilisation): The specifications of the Samsung Galaxy Note 10 Lite are summarised in the table below. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-336782" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Galaxy-Note-10-Lite-1.jpg" alt="Galaxy Note 10 Lite 1" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Galaxy-Note-10-Lite-1.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Galaxy-Note-10-Lite-1-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Galaxy-Note-10-Lite-1-300x202.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-336784" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Galaxy-Note-10-Lite-2.jpg" alt="Galaxy Note 10 Lite 2" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Galaxy-Note-10-Lite-2.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Galaxy-Note-10-Lite-2-595x400.jpg 595w, https://mybroadband.